<br>
I will never forget Crowl on Eci coming from Lavastorm on a raid to East Wastes because I was shoutin for a res.  I had JUST hit 36, and undinged.  I needed the exp back, i COULDNT stand another second of 35.  I have NO idea how he heard i needed a res, but he came!<br>
<br>
Like I said, those with epics .. that is just wrong if they wont res :)  <br>
<br>
I still offer 50p for resses, and will.  The time you save me with exp is worth 50p.  By the time resses matter (level 35-40 or so)..you have the extra 50p to give someone.  Time is valuble.  For both ther resser, and the ressee :)  If you get be back 1/2 a blue bubble at 45, that's maybe a full day of playing.  50p, shoot yeah :)  At post 50, dropping 50p for a res is MORE than worth it.<br>
<br>
Turn it down if you want, I'm offering it :)<br>
<br>
My personal feeling is i wont EVER charge.  If I have the mana, and it wont cause significant downtime for my group if i am in one, and you bring me the corpse (unless it's impossible), I'll revive (and eventually res) you.  If you offer me a thankyou, I will graciously accept. <br>
<br>
Remember, a donation is a token of appreciation.  Giving someone a Peridot, some gear you have and done need, or even 10-20p is better than nothing.<br>
<br>
By the way ... word to the wise .. res the druids :)  WHile some of you have druids in guild or your own or your "spouse" ... you never wanna be doing this<br>
