<br>
Lemme share a story (this happened on the Rathe).  I was goofin around and ended up in Lower Guk because someone had asked me for rez's.  I zone in with FM.  Seeing the bods at the zone, I knew I was gonna be there a while.  I was shortly OOM, of course, but there were still others that needed rez.  I guess I'd been there approx 2 hours (yes, rez'ing as quickly as I could), when I noticed a comment said by a cleric (who'd been there *maybe* 15 mins).  I had recently helped a young monk with Raster and I was trying to get to a rogue who had died (I barely escaped by gating).  She'd said something like &quot;Gee, some people ignoring somethingsomething almost makes me ashamed to be a cleric&quot;  I blinked.  I scrolled (apparently, she'd asked for someone to rez soandso and I'd missed it in all the purple on my screen).  I went off on this cleric.  I mean, really.  Here's this n00b insulting the 2 hours I'd just spent rez'in people, and was in the process of /t'ing another to find out where the corpse was, and this (*#$ had the gall to say something like that to my face!  PFFT!<br>
<br>
Okies, wehre was I?  Oh yeah!  But me not stupid, either.  I will accept donations, monetary or just a heartfelt thanks.  Those that cannot even bestir themselves to say Thank You go to the bottom of the rez list, or even crossed off &lt;grin&gt;.</font><P><center><font face="Monotype Corsiva" size="5" color="#C0C0C0"><strong>Edwina Nytengayle<br> </strong></font></center>

